                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>New York</placeName>\n                <date>29<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> Oct. 1855</date>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <date>7<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> Heshvan<add>?</add> 5615</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Revd. I. Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dear Sir.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Your favor of<lb/>\n                <date>3d. Heshvan</date> I duly received. It is true<lb/> that some remarks made by\n                you<lb/> in conversation at the house of <persName>Mr Lyons</persName><lb/> on the\n                night after <date>Kippur</date> have been<lb/> made the subject of conversation in<lb/>\n                <placeName>New York</placeName>. Opinions so new &amp; startling<lb/> (however\n                correct) from a teacher generally<lb/> considered so orthodox as the <persName>Revd\n                    I Leeser</persName><lb/> were naturally discussed and commented<lb/> upon both\n                by those who heard them<lb/> and those to whom they were repeated.<lb/> And now\n                after reading your expla-<lb/>-nation of them, I am unable to</p>\n            "
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3qf8k51s/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
