                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n            <p>discover that the tongue of Slander<lb/> has been wagging—that the vile<lb/> &amp;\n                malicious have been at work<lb/> or that mischief makers are among<lb/> us.</p>\n            <p>You are quoted as having said<lb/> at <persName>Mr. Lyons</persName> (and to others) that<lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">you</hi> would marry a <sic>christian</sic><lb/> girl having\n                Jewish blood by<lb/> descent in the female line to any<lb/> Jew young man—this you\n                do<lb/> not deny, but on the contrary<lb/> maintain to be good law by precept<lb/>\n                and authority. I shall be<lb/> happy to lay your letter before<lb/> any who allude\n                to the subject<lb/> to afford them the opportunity of<lb/> judging of the soundness\n                of your<lb/> doctrines.</p>\n            <p>with my best wishes for your<lb/> welfare I am dear sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(5)\">Yours very respectfully</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(5)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Benjn Nathan</persName>\n            </p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>\n"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3qf8k51s/canvas/p2"
